records.addlTxt: Agreement for Modification to Conditions of Probation

Defendant Julie M. Yerken in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 11:12 a.m. State moves to amend ct 1 to misd possess drug paraphernalia 961.573(1). Def will plead to cts 1, 2 and 4, ct 3 dismiss w/out prejudice, withheld sentence on each ct, 2 yrs probation, concurrent, costs, no DNA surcharge, cooperate with Social Services. Atty Laufenberg and Def agree. State advises no victim rights requirements. Court reviews plea quest. and constitutional rights. Plea to amended ct 1 - no contest. Ct 2 no contest plea. Ct 4 no contest plea. Elements reviewed. Atty Laufenberg satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Statement by Atty Laufenberg. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds guilty of cts 1 & 2 misd possess drug paraphernalia and ct 4 neglecting a child. Nothing by Def. Court accepts agreement.  Ct 1 -Withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, court costs, cooperate with Social Services. Same sentence for cts 2 and 4. Court grants amendment of ct 1 if not already done. Probation concurrent. Return bond to poster.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. No credit for time served. Postconviction rights. Ct 3 dismissed without prejudice.

Attorney Wright C. Laufenberg in court.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 11:04 a.m. Def is in custody in another county.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for April 8, 2015 at 09:00 am.

Attorney Wright C. Laufenberg in court.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 10:53 a.m. Statement by Atty Laufenberg. State advises Def in custody in another county. Bond remains.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for February 11, 2015 at 11:15 am.
